One point is measured every dt = 0.01 s. The number of points N is therefore equal to N = T ∕dt, where T is the experimental time (indicated in the figures for each test. N = 10000 with the sliding mass for example).
6.2. Angles measurement during the experiments
Let La be the list of measured angles La = {α, β, γ, μ, η, φ}. For the experiment, the angles were measured using two methods: qualisys system to obtain an accurate measurement and IMUs to show the validity of the method.
6.2.1. Angles measurement with qualisys system
