An ideal measurement would be to take P0 = O and P1 = P2 = B to evaluate La. However, for several reasons such as the fact that B is sliding, these points may be difficult or impossible to measure in practice without a motion capture system. Thus, the proposed method was evaluated by taking points such that a sensor could be installed at these positions. These ‘‘sensors’’ positions have to be chosen such that
1. they must avoid blocking the movement of the sliding element on the umbilical as much as possible, 2. they are far enough to obtain a good estimate of the umbilical orientation, 3. the distance between the sensor and the axis of rotation of the angles it measures is realistic.
